---
/**
 * TFStateVisual.astro
 * Terraform state management concepts
 */
---

<div class="tfs-wrap">
  <h3 class="tfs-title">Terraform State — What Can Go Wrong</h3>
  <div class="tfs-items">
    <div class="tfs-item" style="--i:0; --color:#ef4444;">
      <div class="tfs-icon">💥</div>
      <div class="tfs-body">
        <div class="tfs-name">Local State File</div>
        <div class="tfs-desc">terraform.tfstate on your laptop. Team member runs apply concurrently → state corruption. Laptop dies → state lost.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tfs-item" style="--i:1; --color:#f59e0b;">
      <div class="tfs-icon">🔒</div>
      <div class="tfs-body">
        <div class="tfs-name">Remote Backend + Locking</div>
        <div class="tfs-desc">State stored in S3/GCS. DynamoDB/Consul lock prevents concurrent applies. Team-safe, recoverable.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tfs-item" style="--i:2; --color:#4ade80;">
      <div class="tfs-icon">🏗️</div>
      <div class="tfs-body">
        <div class="tfs-name">Workspaces</div>
        <div class="tfs-desc">Same config, multiple environments (dev/staging/prod). Each workspace gets its own state file.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tfs-item" style="--i:3; --color:#06b6d4;">
      <div class="tfs-icon">📦</div>
      <div class="tfs-body">
        <div class="tfs-name">State Per Component</div>
        <div class="tfs-desc">Separate state for networking, compute, database. Blast radius contained. Change DB without risking VPC.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .tfs-wrap{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0f172a,#1e293b);border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:16px;padding:2rem;margin:2rem 0}
  .tfs-title{color:#f1f5f9;text-align:center;font-size:1.25rem;margin:0 0 1.25rem}
  .tfs-items{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:.75rem}
  .tfs-item{display:flex;gap:.75rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.03);border:1px solid var(--color);border-radius:12px;padding:1rem;opacity:0;animation:tfsFade .4s ease forwards;animation-delay:calc(var(--i)*.12s)}
  @keyframes tfsFade{from{opacity:0;transform:translateX(-12px)}to{opacity:1;transform:translateX(0)}}
  .tfs-icon{font-size:1.3rem;flex-shrink:0}
  .tfs-body{flex:1}
  .tfs-name{color:var(--color);font-weight:700;font-size:.9rem;margin-bottom:.2rem}
  .tfs-desc{color:#94a3b8;font-size:.8rem;line-height:1.5}
</style>
